      "writtenOn": "2021-05-13T00:09:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My test subject is the Eros Q. So with ACTION_STD_PREVREPEAT/NEXTREPEAT uncommented, exempting seek from the keylock causes a held seek/skip button to move the cursor in the menu when locked.\n\nSimilarly, with ACTION_STD_PREV/NEXT uncommented, exempting skip from the keylock causes a press of seek/skip (or the scrollwheel) to move the cursor in the menu when locked.\n\nI don\u0027t think it\u0027s desirable to be able to move the cursor when the device is locked anyway - isn\u0027t that the point of a keylock?",
      "parentUuid": "ffcec5a2_aeb88f46",
      "revId": "2843c3ab4b486bed65be5d2710fb0fee28dcaf99",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
